The hunt continues for at least two more suspects in connection with the murder of Hillary Gardee. eNCA has learned of a second arrest after a suspect was detained on Friday. eNCA reporter Pule Letshiwti-Jones has more. #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The hunt continues for more suspects in connection with the murder of Hillary Gardee. eNCA has learned of a third arrest after two other suspects were arrested. The suspects will appear in the Nelspruit magistrate's court on Monday. READ: Second suspect arrested for Gardee murder Speaking at Gardee's funeral service on Saturday, EFF leader Julius Malema said bail for suspects must be opposed. Gardee's body was found days after she had been reported missing. The motive for her killing is still unclear. EFF WELCOMES THE ARREST OF THREE SUSPECTS IN THE HILLARY GARDEE CASE pic.twitter.com/5Z3dRghlJg